content.description: The signed block window for being jailed is currently at 50% of 100 blocks which means that downtime of a few minutes will lead to your node being jailed. This proposal increases the signed block window to 10000 to give more time to fix any issues before being jailed as well as reducing the MinSignedPerWindow and SlashFractionDowntime parameters to more standard values.
content.title: Update Jailing Parameters
